Tips). Transfer onto prepared plate to drain."},{"content":"Place garlic, cucumber and mint into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add yoghurt, coriander, cumin, remaining 2 pinches chilli flakes and remaining ½ teaspoon salt and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Arrange beetroot slices in a single layer onto a serving platter. Top with fried sweet potato and ginger. Garnish with alfafa sprouts (optional) and black sesame seeds (optional). Serve with dressing on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["We used a mandoline to slice our beetroot.","Take care when frying the ginger and sweet potato as they can burn easily."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","35m","4 portions"]}